{
  "text": "Inhibition of the Wnt pathway by secreted DKK1 has been shown to initiate carciogenesis in vertebrate embryos [CITATION_1] , and the overexpression of DKK1 has been described in multiple myeloma, hepatoblastoma and Wilms' tumor, as well as prostate, kidney, breast, lung (3) and esophageal cancers [CITATION_2] . The classification of types of lung cancer is based on multiple clinicopathological features [CITATION_3] . However, such clinical information may be incomplete or misleading in the determination of patient prognosis [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
